\begin_layout Section*
Abstract
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
“Change Data Capture (CDC)” is a near-real-time data integration technique that propagates incremental modifications from source databases to target systems,
 minimizing latency and computational load.
 This project proposes the design of a CDC-centric architecture as a foundation for big data applications requiring an alternative to traditional batch file processing and complex ETL/ELT approaches.
 As a use case,
 the design is applied to a recommendation system for the “Magento” e-commerce platform,
 which uses 
\shape italic
Debezium
\shape default
 and 
\shape italic
Kafka
\shape default
 as ingestion layer,
 
\shape italic
Apache Spark
\shape default
 as analytical layer,
 an api and a web application in python as presentation layer,
 and finally,
 
\shape italic
Mongo
\shape default
 database as the central storage layer.
 The methodology includes:
 (1)
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

selection of CDC technology,
 (2)
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

design of a data ingestion pipeline for product data,
 and (3)
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

implementation of a product recommendation system based on this design.
 Preliminary results highlight the solution’s scalability and flexibility compared to traditional replication methods.
 This work provides a framework applicable in environments where real-time personalization is critical,
 such as e-commerce,
 auditing,
 and data migrations.
